description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen for a successful candidate to join our Facilities Team in delivering Housekeeping Services with an Acute Hospital Setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position will support the Facilities (Hotel Services) team in delivering housekeeping and linen room services to the National Standards for Cleanliness in NHS Wales, HIW standard 5 and organisational standards. To assist in developing, maintaining and promoting the highest standards of service delivery and team working practices, supporting the Facilities Unit commitment to the EQMS framework and helping to maintain open, effective communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be allocated to a ward or department area, or work as part of the Rapid Response and Additional Cleaning team. This team supports the housekeeping service by providing a pre-determined programme of additional cleaning activities using designated equipment and providing a rapid response to infection outbreak situations in accordance to instruction from the housekeeping supervisor and the Infection Prevention and Control team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Housekeeping and Cleanliness duties will be routinely carried out in accordance with the Health Board Housekeeping standard operating procedure and roles and responsibilities for cleaning procedure of which standards are subject to regular audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is rotered across seven days and is 30.0 hours weekly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Tracey Griffiths Job title Facilities Suppport Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address tracey.EL.Griffiths@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number&lt;/p&gt;
